            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ There will be no difficulty, dear Mr Gill, to realize your wish, that a new plant should be named after you, because among  ¶ minute ¶   ¶ weeds ¶ , which come up in early spring many absolute nove...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">89.00.00l</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Walter Gill</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M33, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <table n="Table1">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">None of the specimens named are now at MEL and so the date of the letter cannot be inferred from collection dates. Specimens numbered 7-30 are listed in M to W. Gill, 14 December 1888, while specimens 35-38 are listed in M to W. Gill, 20 August 1889. M's lists broadly follow the sequence of Gill's collection numbers, and the Item is dated to 1889 on the presumption that it preceded the August 1889 list; it is not possible, however, to infer the likely month.</p>
               </note>
               <row>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.0556in; padding-right: 0.0556in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
                        xml:lang="en">34,</p>
                  </cell>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.0556in; padding-right: 0.0556in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <name key="Spergularia%20rubra">Spergularia rubra</name>, Persoon.</p>
                  </cell>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.0556in; padding-right: 0.0556in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
                        xml:lang="en">33,</p>
                  </cell>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.0556in; padding-right: 0.0556in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <name key="Goodenia%20albiflora">Goodenia albiflora</name>, Schlechtendal.</p>
                  </cell>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.0556in; padding-right: 0.0556in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
                        xml:lang="en">32,</p>
                  </cell>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.0556in; padding-right: 0.0556in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <name key="Cynanchum%20floribundum">Cynanchum floribundum</name>, RBrown.</p>
                  </cell>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.0556in; padding-right: 0.0556in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
                        xml:lang="en">31.</p>
                  </cell>
                  <cell style="padding-left: 0.0556in; padding-right: 0.0556in; padding-top: 0in; padding-bottom: 0in; border: none; ">
                     <p rend="letter"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <name key="Aster%20axillaris">Aster axillaris</name>, F.v.Mueller.</p>
                  </cell>
               </row>
            </table>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>There will be no difficulty, dear Mr Gill, to realize your wish, that a new plant should be named after you, because among <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">minute</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">weeds</hi>
               </seg>, which come up in early spring many absolute novelties must yet occur there. But all your plants for such purposes, should be collected as well in <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">fruit</hi>
               </seg> as in flower.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">No species named by M for Gill has been found (IPNI, accessed 10 February 2021). </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Decades of the Acacias<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B87.13.08, B88.13.10.</p>
               </note> and what you want of the Decades of the Eucalypts<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">It is not known which decades Gill required; the final decade was B84.11.02.</p>
               </note> can be obtained from the Gov Printing Office here by purchase; or you might instruct a South-Australian Bookseller, to order these publications for you from the Melbourne Gov. Printing Office. I purchase there for private gifts over £50 -. - annually myself on my own expenses</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With best compliments your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
